          ><div data-instant-type="text" class="instant-rich-text ieqLGJ6BqGZQZ2NOC"><h3>Privacy Policy</h3></div
          ><div data-instant-type="text" class="instant-rich-text icFXfVmWhk7u7X1lj"
            ><p>This Privacy Policy explains how our website, <strong>The Bedtimes</strong> (our "Website"), collects, uses, protects, and discloses information gathered from users.</p><p>1. Who We Are</p><p>Our Website address is: thebedtimes.co</p><p>2. Collection of Personal Data</p><p>Comments</p><p>When visitors submit comments on the Website, we collect the data displayed in the comments form. We also collect the visitor’s IP address and browser user agent string. This information is processed to facilitate spam detection.</p><p>An anonymized string generated from your email address (known as a hash) may be shared with the Gravatar service to verify its use. The Gravatar service privacy policy can be accessed here: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="instant-editor__link" href="https://automattic.com/privacy/">https://automattic.com/privacy/</a>. Upon approval of your comment, your profile picture associated with the Gravatar service becomes publicly visible alongside your comment.</p><p>Media</p><p>If you choose to upload images to the Website, we advise against uploading images that contain embedded location data (EXIF GPS). Visitors to the Website are able to download and extract any location data present in images posted on the site.</p><p>Cookies</p><p>We utilize cookies to enhance the user experience and service functionality:</p
            ><ul
              ><li
                ><p><strong>Commenter Convenience:</strong> If you leave a comment, you may opt-in to save your name, email address, and website details via cookies. These cookies are stored for your convenience to prevent the necessity of re-entering your details for future comments and will persist for one year.</p></li
              ><li
                ><p><strong>Temporary/Session Cookies:</strong> A temporary cookie is set upon visiting our login page to determine if your browser supports cookies. This cookie does not contain personal data and is automatically discarded when you close your browser.</p></li
              ><li
                ><p><strong>Login &amp; Preferences:</strong> Upon logging in, several cookies are established to store your login credentials and screen display preferences. Login cookies are retained for two days, and screen options cookies last for one year. Selecting the "Remember Me" option extends the login persistence to two weeks. Logging out of your account removes the associated login cookies.</p></li
              ><li
                ><p><strong>Article Editing:</strong> If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie is saved in your browser. This cookie contains no personal data and is used solely to indicate the post ID of the article recently edited. It expires after 1 day.</p></li
              ></ul
            ><p>Embedded content from other websites</p><p>Articles and content published on this site may contain embedded content (such as videos, images, or articles) originating from external websites. Embedded content operates identically to how it would if the visitor directly accessed the originating external website.</p><p>These external websites may independently collect data about you, utilize cookies, embed further third-party tracking mechanisms, and monitor your interaction with their embedded content, especially if you possess an account and are logged into that specific external website.</p><p>3. Data Sharing and Disclosure</p><p>Password Resets</p><p>If you initiate a request for a password reset, your IP address will be included within the password reset email sent to you.</p><p>Automated Spam Detection</p><p>Visitor comments may be subjected to scrutiny by an automated spam detection service.</p><p>4. Data Retention Policy</p
            ><ul
              ><li
                ><p><strong>Comments:</strong> If you leave a comment, both the comment and its corresponding metadata are retained indefinitely. This enables us to automatically recognize and approve any follow-up comments, bypassing the moderation queue process.</p></li
              ><li
                ><p><strong>Registered Users (if applicable):</strong> For any users who register an account on our Website, we store the personal information provided within their user profile. All registered users maintain the ability to view, modify, or delete their personal information at any time (with the sole exception of their username). Website administrators are also authorized to view and edit this information.</p></li
              ></ul
            ><p>5. Your Rights Over Your Data</p><p>If you hold an active account on this Website or have previously left comments, you have the right to request:</p
            ><ol
              ><li
                ><p><strong>A copy of data:</strong> An exported file containing the personal data we hold about you, which includes any data you have directly provided to us.</p></li
              ><li
                ><p><strong>Erasure of data:</strong> The deletion of any personal data we hold about you.</p></li
              ></ol
            ><p>This right to erasure does not extend to any data we are legally, administratively, or securely obliged to retain.</p></div
          ></div
